One final strategic recommendation

At this stage, I would stop designing additional modules and shift into execution architecture. The highest-value work now is to produce:

A master domain-driven architecture (bounded contexts and service boundaries).
A canonical data model shared across platforms.
Enterprise event contracts (e.g., LoanApproved, JournalPosted, CustomerUpdated).
UI/UX design system with reusable enterprise components.
Engineering standards for APIs, security, testing, observability, and AI integration.
A phased implementation roadmap (MVP → Enterprise → Banking Edition).

Those artifacts will determine whether ARTH.OS remains a large collection of modules or becomes a maintainable, scalable enterprise platform that can realistically compete in the banking and NBFC market.